[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Assessing reflection in tests**\n\nI’m looking into a dynamic report call that doesn’t seem to use a public API. It feels like reflection might be getting tricky here; existing tests are using it, but maybe they’re not addressing the right things. Increasingly, I'm wondering if I should create a Groovy test, although tests are primarily in Java. There are some uncertainties about invoking methods and how they interact with the runtime. I need to refine the process for calling the class effectively.\n\n**Investigating method invocation issues**\n\nI’m figuring out that using direct method.invoke might generate a Method.invoke rather than reaching the target Class.forName. The JVM agent should ideally see the target when invoked, but what’s puzzling is why it’s newly unaddressed. It's possible that the test didn’t compile or run, or maybe reflection fails due to accessibility issues. I need to examine the test reports for dynamic access and inspect build reports to clarify what might have changed in the process.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0d528c1604729370016a27d2010aa08195ac45205e174f09ea\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJ9IMYyoUsA3Fe2jWG3PDvqo1rC9-xKFAz5lzH5ztaCfs7SXq1p54uZWQ8JiJBYkrnSvCCPlNOR3qYzC22j4sWOiyCpMHbFfc2mN7EbwRSRbQaz8avQF26ITq0zZf5DR-9uMOd6xLChZIYaNSH6-MEZDHNsVydVhaWHHdkcGPVSD96MWgnX7JuNfIpp-CvtY86R3fkbGZarVSFj7sZzB7u6g0HQn2KICwRvTjDkwn3nqAH9RxHKpyUCfBS1wRojZTEEL7uwo59X1jwYS7gA7G5UY9a1DU00n7kN8OXjfG28svzeMkBO8NVnXZVBwLmT_258nnbr-zA8QL3bihNVZpDiBzSab5dnAWlLBc1kMLBO5j6TThJ7i4VHPS90shqaTveDLeLrA-S80V0s7z52DVnBnEllhhMlosX2H3m6aDFhdlDYldkt1MuzbZtwO3KrkLvUdeM9iFk3CUIBLXPmIUt_S6vqreWWWaY7LZLQPXmJ0GA57uKVB-kzONuYW8OIl7ns3TErGyMPs9b07FdQKbboYUROAZlvZbOOkGsMRqTQOktD6ozFKmy0WL_6xK3g0QXnRhxlnEQTCJPDatdjEsr-7oFTE1Jwsv48McAIxmWUIod7Cr_WQDGSOpXcmfFmcqZqmthLQbjmxxHdEANow8NHYi35tIlL91Es2vBG0f00u7WRcWpGgZaslnPaOb_X